  "body": "None of the logging parameters are effective when specified in a toml file and read in via --config flag during runtime. Other parameters are read in (some need quotes).\r\n\r\n```\r\ndatadir = \"/erigon/data\"\r\nport = \"{{PEER_PORT}}\"\r\nchain = \"{{NETWORK}}\"\r\nhttp = \"true\"\r\n\r\n\"log.dir.verbosity\" = 4\r\n\"log.console.verbosity\" = 0\r\n\"log.dir.path\" = \"/erigon/data/\"\r\n\r\n\"http.addr\" = \"0.0.0.0\"\r\n\"http.api\" = \"engine,eth,erigon,web3,net,debug,trace,txpool\"\r\n\"http.port\" = \"{{RPC_PORT}}\"\r\n\"http.corsdomain\" = \"*\"\r\n\r\n\"authrpc.jwtsecret\" = \"/erigon/config/jwt.hex\"\r\n\"authrpc.addr\" = \"0.0.0.0\"\r\n\"authrpc.port\" = {{AUTH_PORT}}\r\n\"authrpc.vhosts\" = \"*\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nI have tried\r\n[log]\r\ndir.path = ... \r\n\r\nWith quotes and without, upper and lower case. Also tried \"log.dir.path\" = ... with and without quotes to no avail. None of the other logging parameters work either, including verbosity for console and dir. Tried with latest version, 2.29.0",
